#compdef observable
# =============================================================================
# observable — Observable Inc.'s "A static site generator
#              for data apps, dashboards, reports, and
#              more" — the CLI for Observable Framework,
#              a static site generator combining
#              JavaScript on the front-end (for
#              interactive D3 / Plot / Mosaic / Plotly
#              visualizations) with any language on the
#              back-end (Python / R / Julia / SQL /
#              Markdown / JavaScript) for data analysis.
#              Observable Framework is the open-source
#              successor to Observable Notebooks
#              (observablehq.com), bringing the same
#              reactive-cell programming model to a
#              standalone static site generator
#              consumable as a regular npm package.
#              Distinguishing from Quarto (Posit's R/
#              Python literate-programming SSG),
#              Jupyter Book (executable Jupyter
#              notebooks → HTML), Streamlit (Python web
#              app), Dash (Python plotly dashboards),
#              Pluto.jl (Julia reactive notebooks), and
#              Datasette (SQL-driven publishing) by:
#                - REACTIVE CELL MODEL — Observable's
#                  signature paradigm: cells are
#                  dependency-tracked + re-evaluate
#                  automatically when inputs change.
#                  The front-end JS runtime reproduces
#                  this for any cell that uses
#                  Observable's reactivity primitives
#                - POLYGLOT DATA LOADERS — any executable
#                  file (Python, R, Julia, shell, SQL,
#                  Node.js) named `<name>.json.py` or
#                  `<name>.csv.sql` etc. runs at build
#                  time and produces the named data file
#                  that other cells can import
#                - D3 + PLOT + MOSAIC INTEGRATION — first-
#                  class support for Observable's own D3
#                  + Plot (declarative chart grammar) +
#                  Mosaic (high-perf data viz) libraries
#                - MINISEARCH-POWERED SEARCH — uses
#                  lucaong/minisearch for client-side
#                  full-text search over the generated
#                  site's content (this is the headline
#                  CLI library that closes Axis 30 on
#                  the TS-Node side; see taxonomy notes
#                  below)
#                - CLACK PROMPTS — uses @clack/prompts
#                  for the interactive `observable
#                  create` scaffolding wizard
#                - WEBSOCKET PREVIEW SERVER — `observable
#                  preview` starts a dev server with
#                  hot-reload via WebSockets (Axis 18
#                  covered); changes to Markdown files
#                  + data loaders propagate to the
#                  browser in real-time
#                - STATIC OUTPUT FOR ANY HOST — `observable
#                  build` produces a fully-static site
#                  in dist/ that deploys to Netlify /
#                  Vercel / Cloudflare Pages / GitHub
#                  Pages / S3 / any static host
#                - DEPLOY TO OBSERVABLE — `observable
#                  deploy` (deprecated as of 2026) pushed
#                  to Observable's hosted service for
#                  authenticated viewing; superseded by
#                  community-maintained static hosting
#                - NOTEBOOK CONVERTER — `observable
#                  convert <notebook-url-or-file>`
#                  transforms an Observable Notebook
#                  (the SaaS product) into Markdown
#                  + .js files for use in Framework
#                - YAML + JSON CONFIG — observablehq.config
#                  .{js,ts,json,yaml} configures site
#                  metadata, theme, deploy target,
#                  navigation
#                - PARSEARGS RUNTIME — uses Node.js's
#                  built-in node:util parseArgs (Node 22+)
#                  instead of commander/yargs for CLI
#                  parsing; demonstrates the modern
#                  stdlib approach
#              Used by: data scientists publishing
#              interactive reports + dashboards (DJ
#              Patil, Hilary Mason et al's "Data
#              Visualization Society" community),
#              journalism teams (The Pudding, NYT) for
#              data-driven story publishing, and
#              analysts replacing static PDF reports
#              with interactive HTML.
#
# Author:  Observable Inc.  Lead author: Mike Bostock
#          (mbostock; creator of D3, Observable Notebooks).
#          Active development with frequent releases.
#          License: ISC (was Apache-2.0 in early
#          releases).
# Source:  https://github.com/observablehq/framework
#          https://github.com/observablehq/framework/blob/main/src/bin/observable.ts
#          https://observablehq.com/framework/
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; documentation at
#          https://observablehq.com/framework/.
# Library: minisearch (Luca Ongaro's tiny client-side
#          full-text search engine — the headline
#          dependency for this completion's axis-closing
#          role; see taxonomy notes below).  Also
#          node:util parseArgs (Node 22+ stdlib; Axis 1
#          argparse), @clack/prompts (Axis 8 prompts),
#          chokidar (Axis 17 file watching), esbuild
#          (bundler), gray-matter (YAML front-matter),
#          markdown-it (Axis 19 markdown), js-yaml (Axis
#          20 YAML), wrap-ansi (Axis 12 textwrap).
# License: ISC
# Status:  3,498+ stars on observablehq/framework;
#          production-deployed by Observable Inc. +
#          The Pudding + various data-journalism teams +
#          analytics platforms.
